  "text": "We can still color the local surface by the other scalar or particle fields, such as temperature or pressure, but we can also generate new scalar fields to represent differences between the focus values and the absolute values. When dealing with dense, unstructured particle fields, we can interpolate the particles on a uniform grid using weighted aver-aging or moving least squares. We utilize CUDA and GPU hardware to speed up the calculation, similar to [CITATION_1] .",
